        <name>1.1.4.2 Multiplication and Division with Negative Numbers</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fully simplify without using a calculator&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(-{@a1@} \times 3 =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\({@a1@} \times -3 =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(-{@a1@} \times -3 =\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@a2@}}{-3} =\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@a3@}}{7} =\) [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@a4@}}{-12} =\) [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]] [[feedback:prt6]]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The product of a negative and a positive is a negative \(\implies -{@a1@} \times 3 = {@ta1@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The product of a positive and a negative is a negative \(\implies {@a1@} \times -3 = {@ta2@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The product of a negative and a negative is a negative \(\implies -{@a1@} \times -3 = {@ta3@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dividing a positive number by a negative number gives a negative number \(\implies \dfrac{{@a2@}}{-3} = {@ta4@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dividing a negative number by a positive number gives a negative number \(\implies \dfrac{{@a3@}}{7} = {@ta5@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dividing a negative number by a negative number gives a positive number \(\implies \dfrac{{@a4@}}{-12} = {@ta6@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
